Project Objectives

- Deploy a Windows Server 2022 domain controller (`server1`).  
- Configure a multi‑role server supporting AD DS, DNS, DHCP, WDS, WINS, DFS, NPS, VPN, CA, WSUS, and iSCSI.  
- Install a second server (`server2`) from WDS and join it to the domain.  
- Build advanced enterprise DHCP, DNS, GPO, and OU structures.  
- Implement secure and scalable enterprise networking services.  
- Configure storage, replication, trust relationships, and multi‑site AD topology.  
- Generate administrative reports using PowerShell. 

Technologies Used

- Windows Server 2022  
- Windows 11  
- Active Directory Domain Services  
- DNS, DHCP, WINS  
- WDS / PXE Deployment  
- VPN / NPS (RADIUS)  
- DFS Namespace + DFS Replication  
- Certificate Services (AD CS)  
- iSCSI Target & Data Deduplication  
- WSUS  
- Hyper‑V Virtualization  
- PowerShell Administration 
